                        <p>
                            For well over a decade, the United States military maintained a strong and active presence in Afghanistan as it battled the Taliban and other terrorist groups in the region. Even as the U.S. withdraws a large portion of its military from the region, in 2015 President Barack Obama announced plans in 2015 to have approximately 10,000 troops remain in Afghanistan for several more years. 
